proxies
=======

RUBY GEMS
=========
SET HTTP_PROXY=http://%USER%:%PASSWORD%@%SERVER%:%PORT%
SET HTTP_PROXY=http://wolfbyte:secret@pigsy:8080
or 
gem install -p http://proxy_ip:proxy_port rails


GIT
===
git config --global http.proxy http://mydomain\\myusername:mypassword@myproxyserver:8080


AWS-SDK
=======
# http://aws.amazon.com/releasenotes/Ruby/9162810565754481
AWS.config(:proxy_uri => 'https://user:password@my.proxy:443/path?query')


HEROKU
======
If youâ€™re behind a firewall that requires use of a proxy to connect with external HTTP/HTTPS services, you can set the HTTP_PROXY or HTTPS_PROXY environment variables before running the heroku command.


TWILIO
======
opts = {
	:proxy_addr => nil,
    :proxy_port => nil,
    :proxy_user => nil,
    :proxy_pass => nil,
}
client = Twilio::REST::Client.new account_sid, auth_token, opts